Biden to get progressives' pitch for national security hires 
 
By BRYAN BENDER   
 
12/18/2020 10:00 AM EST 
 
Presented by Northrop Grumman 
 
With Connor O’Brien 
 
Editor’s Note: Morning Defense is a free version of POLITICO Pro Defense's morning newsletter, which is delivered to our subscribers each morning at 6 a.m. The POLITICO Pro platform combines the news you need with tools you can use to take action on the day’s biggest stories. Act on the news with POLITICO Pro . 
Quick Fix 
 
— Progressives line up their own national security recruits for Biden with a diverse roster of recommendations to fill key jobs. 
 
— The massive hack of U.S. government networks included intrusions into the nation’s nuclear weapons complex. 
 
— It looks like a temporary government shutdown as congressional leaders work out spending and coronavirus aid deals. 
 
