Making Moves 
 
Eric Sayers, a former special assistant to the commander at U.S. Pacific Command and staffer on the Senate Armed Services Committee, is now a visiting fellow at the American Enterprise Institute. He also remains a vice president at Beacon Strategies. 
 
The Center for a New American Security also announced six new adjunct fellows , including retired Air Force Gen. Mike Holmes , a senior adviser at The Roosevelt Group; Nina Kollars of the Naval War College; Jenny McArdle at Improbable LLC; Tom Shugart, the former military adviser in the Pentagon Office of Net Assessment; Erik Lin-Greenberg of MIT; and Rachel Tecott at George Washington University. 
